methods.name: index
methods.full_description:
== Retrieve Bucketlists

This endpoint is used to retrieve a usersâ€™ bucketlists. It optionally takes params to return the bucketlist in pages and the for limit of bucketlists to fetch per request. It could also be queried with a search params to return all bucketlists that match the params.

Authentication token has to be passed as part of the request. It must be passed as HTTP header(TOKEN).

methods.name: create
methods.full_description:
== Create new Bucketlist

This endpoint is used to create a new bucketlist. It requires a name for the new bucketlist.

Authentication token has to be passed as part of the request. It must be passed as HTTP header(TOKEN).

methods.name: show
methods.full_description:
== Show details of a Bucketlist

This endpoint is used to retrieve more details of a given bucketlist such as created_at. It requires a valid user bucketlist id

Authentication token has to be passed as part of the request. It must be passed as HTTP header(TOKEN).

params.name: id
params.description: Id of the user bucketlist to fetch.

methods.name: update
methods.full_description:
== Update a Bucketlist

This endpoint is used to update the details of a given bucketlist. It requires a valid user bucketlist id and new name for the bucketlist.

Authentication token has to be passed as part of the request. It must be passed as HTTP header(TOKEN).

methods.name: destroy
methods.full_description:
== Destroy a Bucketlist

This endpoint is used to delete a bucketlist and all itâ€™s associated items.

Authentication token has to be passed as part of the request. It must be passed as HTTP header(TOKEN).

methods.name: index
methods.full_description:
== Retrieve items

This endpoint is used to retrieve the items in a given checklist. It optionally takes params to return the items in pages and the limit of items to fetch per request. If not provided it defaults to 20 items per query. The max allowed number of items that can be fetched per request is 100. It could also be queried with a status params (i.e â€˜doneâ€™ or â€˜pendingâ€™) to return all items that match the params.

Authentication token has to be passed as part of the request. It must be passed as HTTP header(TOKEN).

params.name: checklist_id
params.description: Id of the checklist item belongs to
